Grant Larson served in the United States Air Force. Grant Larson was a business owner in Jackson, Wyoming. Grant Larson served on the Teton County Commission. An emirate is a political territory that is ruled by a dynastic Arabic or Islamic monarch-styled emir.

Soko Magattara, Sakurazaka? (そこ曲がったら、櫻坂?, "If You Turn There, is it Sakurazaka?") is a Japanese late night variety show starring Japanese idol group Sakurazaka46. a Japanese late night variety show starring Japanese idol group Sakurazaka46 is hosted by Yū Sawabe and Teruyuki Tsuchida and airs every Sunday at 12:35 AM JST on TV Tokyo. a Japanese late night variety show starring Japanese idol group Sakurazaka46 is the direct continuation of Keyakitte, Kakenai?, which had the same cast, format, and time slot, but named after the former name of Japanese idol group Sakurazaka46, Keyakizaka46.

100 años de amor y luz (100 years of love and light),  is a Venezuelan compilation album of 1998, in commemoration  of the 100 years of the birth of Conny Méndez. a Venezuelan compilation album of 1998 presents Conny Méndez's most popular songs.

Gimbap (김밥), also romanized as kimbap, is a Korean dish made from cooked rice and ingredients such as vegetables, fish and meats that are rolled in gim—dried sheets of seaweed—and served in bite-sized slices. The origins of gimbap are debated. Some sources derive gimbap's origin from the Japanese norimaki during the colonial times, while others state gimbap is a modernized version of bokssam from the Joseon era. Regardless, gimbap has since become a distinct dish. gimbap can be easily eaten in bite-sized pieces regardless of location. So gimbap is often part of a packed meal, or dosirak, to be eaten at picnics and outdoor events, and can serve as a light lunch along with danmuji (yellow pickled radish) and kimchi. gimbap is a popular take-out food in South Korea and abroad, and is known as a convenient food because of gimbap's portability.

Qaleh Khvajeh (Persian: قلعه خواجه‎, also Romanized as Qal‘eh Khvājeh, Qal‘eh Khājeh, Qal‘eh Khavājeh, Qal‘eh Khwāja, Qal‘eh-ye Khvājeh, and Qal‘eh-ye Khvājū) is a village in Behnamarab-e Jonubi Rural District, Javadabad District, Varamin County, Tehran Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, Qaleh Khvajeh's population was 1,418, in 316 families.

Gender bias on Wikipedia, also known as the Wikipedia gender gap, refers to the fact that Wikipedia contributors are mostly male, that relatively few biographies on Wikipedia are about women, and that topics of interest to women are less well-covered.In a 2018 survey covering 12 language versions of Wikipedia and some other Wikimedia Foundation projects, 90% of contributors reported 90% of contributors's gender as male, 8.8% as female, and 1% as other. Among contributors to the English Wikipedia, 13.6% identified as female and 1.7% as other. Other studies since 2011, mostly focused on the English Wikipedia, have estimated the percentage of female editors at up to Wikipedia's articles about women are less likely to be included, expanded, neutral, and detailed. The visibility and reachability of women on Wikipedia is  limited, with a 2015 report finding that female pages generally 'tend to be more linked to men'. Language that is considered sexist, loaded, or otherwise gendered has been identified in articles about women. Gender bias features among the most frequent criticisms of Wikipedia, sometimes as part of a more general criticism about systemic bias in Wikipedia.
The 2008 New Jersey Democratic presidential primary took place February 5, 2008, also known as Super Tuesday.  Hillary Clinton won The 2008 New Jersey Democratic presidential primary.
Odontasteridae is a family of sea stars. Members of a family of sea stars are known as cushion stars and have relatively broad discs and five short tapering arms.

The Great Snaefell Mine, also referred to as the East Snaefell Mine, was a zinc mine located high in the Laxey Valley on the slopes of Snaefell Mountain, in the parish of Lonan, Isle of Man. The Great Snaefell Mine reached a depth of 1,188 ft (362 m) and is remembered as the scene of Isle of Man's worst mining disaster in 1897.

Wingett Run is an unincorporated community in western Ludlow Township, Washington County, Ohio, United States.  Wingett Run has a post office with the ZIP code 45789.  Wingett Run is located along State Route 26 and the Little Muskingum River.A post office called Wingett Run was in operation from 1873 to 1993. The name comes from the nearby stream, Wingett Run, which itself was named after an early settler of the region, Jacob Wingett.

Wikipedia is a free multilingual open-source wiki-based online encyclopedia edited and maintained by a community of volunteer editors, started on 15 January 2001 as an English-language encyclopedia. Soon, non-English editions were created: the German and Catalan editions were created on circa 16 March, the French edition was created on 23 March, and the Swedish edition was created on 23 May. As of June 2021, Wikipedia articles have been created in 321 editions, with 310 currently active and 11 closed.The Meta-Wiki language committee, consisting of 16 members, is in charge of managing the policies on creating a new Wikimedia project edition, processing requests, as well as "supporting and coordinating new projects to optimize new projects's success." In order to pass eligibility, a language must have a valid ISO 639 code, be "sufficiently unique," and have a "sufficient number of fluent users to form a viable contributor community and an audience for the content." In order to pass eligibility for closure, an edition should either "don't have content or existing content", or possibly "controversial, questionable or in another way uncommon."

John Henry Lewis (May 1, 1914 – April 18, 1974) was a hall of fame American boxer who held the World Light Heavyweight Boxing Title from 1935 to 1938. The Ring boxing magazine named John Henry Lewis the 16th greatest light heavyweight of all-time. John Henry Lewis's trainer was Larry Amadee, and John Henry Lewis's managers included Ernie Lira, Larry White, Frank Schuler, and Gus Greenlee.
Hydrocotyle, sometimes called water pennywort, Indian pennywort, dollar weed, marsh penny,  thick-leaved pennywort and even white rot

Chorizanthe howellii is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common names Mendocino spineflower and Howell's spineflower. this plant is endemic to coastal Mendocino County, California, where this plant is known only from the sand dunes and coastal scrub near Fort Bragg. It is estimated that 95% of the remaining individuals of this plant are part of a single population growing at MacKerricher State Park. this plant is a federally listed endangered species.

Incarvillea is a genus of about 16 species of flowering plants in the family Bignoniaceae, native to central and eastern Asia, with most of the species growing at high altitudes in the Himalaya and Tibet. The most familiar species is Incarvillea delavayi, a garden plant commonly known as hardy gloxinia or Chinese trumpet flower. Unlike most other members of Bignoniaceae, which are mainly tropical woody plants, species of Incarvillea are herbs from temperate regions.Genetic analysis supports the division of Incarvillea into five clades: the subgenus Niedzwedzkia, the subgenus Amphicome, the subgenus Incarvillea, the subgenus Pteroscleris, and the species I. olgae, which does not fit into a subgenus. the species I. olgae, which does not fit into a subgenus may be given a subgenus of the species I. olgae, which does not fit into a subgenus's own in a future study.Incarvillea is named after the French Jesuit missionary and botanist Pierre Nicholas Le Chéron d'Incarville.Species include:

Żelisławice [ʐɛlʲiswaˈvʲit͡sɛ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Siewierz, within Będzin County, Silesian Voivodeship, in southern Poland. Żelisławice [ʐɛlʲiswaˈvʲit͡sɛ] lies approximately 4 kilometres (2 mi) north of Siewierz, 21 km (13 mi) north-east of Będzin, and 33 km (21 mi) north-east of the regional capital Katowice.

Kutna (pronounced [ˈkuːtna]) is a former village in eastern Slovenia in the Municipality of Trebnje. Kutna is now part of the village of Replje. Kutna is part of the traditional region of Lower Carniola and is now included in the Southeast Slovenia Statistical Region.

Claremont Unified School District is a Los Angeles County school district in Claremont, California. Claremont Unified School District consists of 7 elementary schools, 1 intermediate and 2 high schools, the main one is Claremont High School.
Costa Rica competed at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, United States.  Claudia Poll won Costa Rica's first ever gold medal.

Thoressa astigmata, the southern spotted ace, is a butterfly belonging to the family Hesperiidae. The species was first described by Charles Swinhoe in 1890. The species is endemic to the Western Ghats of India and is found in the states of Kerala, Tamil Nadu and Karnataka.

Faryab Higher Education Institute is a college that was founded in 1977. Faryab promoted pedagogy with education and agriculture faculties. Faryab Higher Education Institute has 637 students, and 36 professors. Faryab Higher Education Institute is a non-profit public higher education institution located in the large town of Maymana (population range of 50,000-249,999 inhabitants), Faryab. Faryab University (FU) is a very small (enrollment range: 500-999 students) coeducational higher education institution.

Murat Rural LLG is a local government area in New Ireland Province, Papua New Guinea. The LLG president is Herman Sole. Murat Rural LLG administers the St. Matthias Group of islands and is located in Kavieng District. Population is 4,210(Census 2011).

The 2nd FINA Synchronised Swimming World Trophy was held 2007 in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The 2nd FINA Synchronised Swimming World Trophy featured swimmers from 8 nations, swimming in three events: Duet, Team and Free Combination.
Knema glaucescens is a species of plant in the family Myristicaceae. It is native to Sumatra, Peninsular Malaysia, Singapore and Borneo.

The fifth season of the mystery music game show Hidden Voices is a Vietnamese spin-off program that officially recognized as part of I Can See Your Voice franchise, which premiered on 28 June 2020 on HTV7.In an official statement with director Khương Dừa in April 2020, it was initially planned to halt production because of the COVID-19 pandemic and thus didn't materialize. Production would continue in The fifth season of the mystery music game show Hidden Voices without audience with enhanced health and safety protocols being implemented.
Pushyaraagam is a 1979 Indian Malayalam film,  directed by C. Radhakrishnan. The film stars Madhu, Jayan, Sharada and Srividya in the lead roles. The film has musical score by A. T. Ummer.

Second Wife is a 1930 American drama film produced and released by RKO Pictures. The film was directed by Russell Mack, written by Hugh Herbert and Bert Glennon, based on the play All the King's Men by Fulton Oursler. The film stars Conrad Nagel and Lila Lee, two silent film veterans moving into talkies.A print of The film is held by the Library of Congress.

Sara Hagström  (born 1995) is a Swedish orienteering competitor. Sara Hagström was born in Skövde.Sara Hagström won individual gold medals at the Junior World Orienteering Championships in 2014 and 2015, and was part of the Swedish team that won the relay in 2014 and 2015. Sara Hagström competed at the 2016 World Orienteering Championships, and won a bronze medal in the relay at the 2018 European Orienteering Championships. Sara Hagström placed sixth in the middle distance at the 2018 World Orienteering Championships in Latvia.

Group D of the 2001 Fed Cup Europe/Africa Zone Group II was one of four pools in the Europe/Africa zone of 2001 Fed Cup. Five teams competed in a round robin competition, with the top team advancing to Group I for 2002.

William Childs Westmoreland (March 26, 1914 – July 18, 2005) was a  United States Army general, most notably commander of United States forces during the Vietnam War from 1964 to 1968. William Childs Westmoreland served as Chief of Staff of United States Army from 1968 to 1972.
Anatole Djekruassem is a Chadian professional football player. Anatole Djekruassem made one appearance for the Chad national football team.
The Liga Ecuatoriana de Baloncesto is the top professional basketball league in Ecuador.

Napua Stevens Poire (born Harriet Daisy Kawaiala Kao'ionapuaopi'ilani Stevens; August 31, 1918 – January 7, 1990) was a Hawaiian entertainer, singer, hula dancer, musician, teacher, radio-television personality, event producer and author. Noted for Napua Stevens Poire's hits such as "Beyond The Reef" and "Hawaiian Hospitality" in the late 1940s, in the 1950s, and later embarked upon a successful media career as a radio DJ for Napua Stevens Poire's own show KTRG and presenting Napua Stevens Poire's own TV cooking show Napua's Kitchen in the 1960s. Napua Stevens Poire made two guest appearances in the popular series Hawaii Five-O and also presented the Aloha Week and Kamehameha Day hula shows.
Anton Zwengauer (11 October 1810 – 13 June 1884) was a German painter of the Biedermeier period.
Dennis Henry Heeke (September 9, 1927 – August 14, 2009) was an American farmer and politician.

Paul Steigerwald (born August 6, 1954) is an Emmy award winning American sportscaster, who through the 2016-17 NHL hockey season worked as the Pittsburgh Penguins' primary television announcer on Root Sports Pittsburgh (now AT&T SportsNet Pittsburgh).

Sarah Cook is a Canadian scholar, who is based in Scotland. Sarah Cook is well known as a historian and curator in the field of New Media art. Sarah Cook was a Research Fellow at the University of Sunderland, where Sarah Cook worked with the research institute CRUMB – Curatorial Resource for Upstart Media Bliss, that Sarah Cook co-founded with Beryl Graham in 2000, and taught on the MA Curating course. In 2013 Sarah Cook was appointed as a Reader and Dundee Research Fellow at Duncan of Jordanstone College of Art, University of Dundee. As part of Sarah Cook's role as Dundee Fellow Sarah Cook founded and curated LifeSpace Science Art Research Gallery in the School of Life Sciences, University of Dundee (2014-2018). Sarah Cook is a trustee of folly in Lancaster.

The Yugoslav Partisans, or the National Liberation Army, officially the National Liberation Army and Partisan Detachments of Yugoslavia, was the Communist-led Anti-fascist resistance to the Axis powers (chiefly Germany) in occupied Yugoslavia during World War II. Led by Josip Broz Tito, The Yugoslav Partisans are considered to be Europe's most effective anti-Axis resistance movement during World War II.Primarily a guerilla force at The Yugoslav Partisans's inception, The Yugoslav Partisans developed into a large fighting force engaging in conventional warfare later in World War II, numbering around 650,000 in late 1944 and were organized in four field armies and 52 divisions. The main stated objectives of The Yugoslav Partisans were the liberation of Yugoslav lands from occupying forces and the creation of a federal, multi-ethnic communist state in Yugoslavia.

The Human Race is an American science fiction action film directed and written by Paul Hough. The Human Race stars Paul McCarthy-Boyington, Eddie McGee and Trista Robinson as a group of people who find a group of people who find themselves forced to race or die forced to race or die. A work-in-progress copy was screened at the 2012 Fantasia Film Festival and the finished copy had the finished copy's world premiere on April 11, 2013 at the Brussels International Fantastic Film Festival.
Scotland in the Middle Ages concerns the history of Scotland from the departure of the Romans to the adoption of major aspects of the Renaissance in the early sixteenth century.

Wilson Township is one of nineteen current townships in Pope County, Arkansas, USA. As of the 2010 census, Wilson Township's unincorporated population was 4,774. Wilson Township now contains the former township of Lee.
Claude "Didi" Andrey (born 13 June 1951 in Genève, Switzerland) is a former Swiss footballer, who most recently managed Yverdon-Sport FC in the Challenge League.
Unimagine is the second album by Australian post-hardcore band Hands Like Houses, released on 23 July 2013 on Rise Records.

Elizabeth Mitchell (born Elizabeth Joanna Robertson; March 27, 1970) is an American actress known for Elizabeth Mitchell's lead role as Juliet Burke on the ABC drama mystery series Lost (2006–2010). Elizabeth Mitchell also had lead roles on the television series V (2009–2010), Revolution (2012–2014), and Dead of Summer (2016), as well as recurring roles as the Snow Queen on Once Upon a Time (2014) and Anna Volovodov on The Expanse (2018).

Unionville High School is a public high school of the York Region District School Board in Ontario, Canada. Unionville High School is located west of the community of Unionville in the city of Markham. Unionville High School is located next to the Markham Civic Centre and the Markham Theatre.

Thomas O'Connor (or O'Conor) (1 September 1770 in Dublin, Ireland – 9 February 1855 in Sands Point, New York) was an Irishman who in 1801 emigrated from County Roscommon, Ireland to New York where Thomas O'Connor (or O'Conor) devoted Thomas O'Connor (or O'Conor) chiefly to journalism.

Not Everybody's Lucky Enough to Have Communist Parents or Tout le monde n'a pas eu la chance d'avoir des parents communistes is a 1993 French comedy film directed by Jean-Jacques Zilbermann and starring Josiane Balasko. Josiane Balasko received Josiane Balasko's second nomination to the César Award for Best Actress for this role.
Çakmaklar is a village in the Ayvacık district of Çanakkale Province in Turkey.
Bulbophyllum forsythianum is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum.

This is a list of composers of 20th-century classical music, sortable by name, year of birth, year of death, nationality, notable works, and remarks. It includes only composers of significant fame and importance. The style of the composer's music is given where possible, bearing in mind that some defy simple classification. Names are listed first by year of birth, then in alphabetical order within each year. The 20th-century is defined by the calendar rather than by any unifying characteristics of musical style or attitude, and is therefore not an era of the same order as the classical or romantic. However, The 20th-century can be divided into modern and postmodern eras that overlap and can be defined more by differences in attitude than style.

Itron is an American technology company that offers products and services on energy and water resource management. Itron's headquarters is in Liberty Lake, Washington, United States. Itron's products and services include technology solutions related to smart grid, smart gas and smart water that measure and analyze electricity, gas and water consumption. Itron's products include electricity, gas, water and thermal energy measurement devices and control technology; communications systems; software; as well as managed and consulting services. Itron has over 8,000 customers in more than 100 countries.
Krumbach is a village in the westernmost Austrian state of Vorarlberg, in the Bregenz district. Krumbach has about 1,000 inhabitants.

Bagabag is an island in the Madang Province of Papua New Guinea having a dormant volcano.Bagabag is 43 km east-north-east from Cape Croilles on the northern coast of the Papua New Guinea mainland, and is the closest island to Karkar Island which is 18 km to the north-west. Bagabag is approximately circular in shape, with a diameter of about 7 km. Bagabag has an area of 37 km². The prominent feature of the coast is New Year Bay, that cuts into the south-eastern side of Bagabag. Volcanic in origin, terrain on Bagabag consists of steep, thickly vegetated slopes that rise to over 600 m above sea level. Much of the northern, eastern and southern coasts are fringed by a barrier-type reef some 2 km offshore; a barrier-type reef some 2 km offshore is narrow, and mostly submerged.

The Canadian province of Newfoundland and Labrador is composed of mainland Labrador and the large island of Newfoundland. The coast of both the large island of Newfoundland and Labrador are lined with islands of various magnitudes.
Sean Gan Giannelli (born 31 October 1996) is a Malaysian footballer who plays as a midfielder or forward for UiTM on loan from Kuala Lumpur City in the Malaysia Super League.

William Allen Smalley (April 4, 1923 – December 16, 1997) was an American linguist. William Allen Smalley is best known for William Allen Smalley's role in the development of the Romanized Popular Alphabet for the Hmong language.

The Royal Navy (RN) is the United Kingdom's naval warfare force. Although warships were used by English and Scottish kings from the early medieval period, the first major maritime engagements were fought in the Hundred Years' War against the Kingdom of France. The Royal Navy (RN) traces The Royal Navy (RN)'s origins to the early 16th century; the oldest of the United Kingdom's's armed services, and The Royal Navy (RN) is, consequently, known as the Senior Service.
Moncarapacho is a former civil parish in the municipality of Olhão, Portugal. In 2013, Moncarapacho merged into the new parish Moncarapacho e Fuseta.
The FIS Alpine World Ski Championships is an alpine skiing competition organized by the International Ski Federation (FIS).

The 55th Wing is a United States Air Force unit assigned to Air Combat Command.  The 55th Wing is primarily stationed at Offutt Air Force Base, Nebraska, but maintains one of The 55th Wing's groups and associated squadrons at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona as a geographically separated unit.

The Province of Las Palmas (, UK: ; Spanish: Provincia de Las Palmas) is a province of Spain, consisting of the eastern part of the autonomous community of the Canary Islands. Las Palmas de Gran Canaria, capital city of The Province of Las Palmas and of the island of Gran Canaria, is the largest city in the autonomous community of the Canary Islands.

Abary is a small community in the Mahaica-Berbice Region of Guyana, near the mouth of the Abary River, 43 miles from Georgetown. Abary is known for the Abary Bridge located on the Main Highway. the Abary Bridge located on the Main Highway was originally a railway bridge and has a very steep ascend. the Abary Bridge located on the Main Highway was designed by Joseph Walter Holder who also built the Demerara Harbour Bridge.

The Fault in Our Stars is a novel by John Green. a novel by John Green is John Green's fourth solo novel, and sixth novel overall. a novel by John Green was published on January 10, 2012. The title is inspired by Act 1, Scene 2 of Shakespeare's play Julius Caesar, in which the nobleman Cassius says to Brutus: "The fault, Brutus, is not in our stars, / But in ourselves, that we are underlings." The story is narrated by Hazel Grace Lancaster, a 16-year-old girl with thyroid cancer that has affected Hazel Grace Lancaster, a 16-year-old girl with thyroid cancer that has affected her lungs's lungs. Hazel Grace Lancaster, a 16-year-old girl with thyroid cancer that has affected her lungs is forced by Hazel Grace Lancaster, a 16-year-old girl with thyroid cancer that has affected her lungs's parents to attend a support group where Hazel Grace Lancaster, a 16-year-old girl with thyroid cancer that has affected her lungs subsequently meets and falls in love with 17-year-old Augustus Waters, an ex-basketball player and amputee.

Most criticism of Wikipedia has been directed towards Wikipedia's content, Wikipedia's community of established users, and Wikipedia's processes. The principal criticism Wikipedia receives concerns Wikipedia's factual reliability, the readability and organization of the articles, the lack of methodical fact-checking, and Wikipedia's exposure to political and biased editing. Concerns have also been raised about systemic bias along gender, racial, political and national lines. In addition, conflicts of interest arising from corporate campaigns to influence content have also been highlighted. Further concerns include the vandalism and partisanship facilitated by anonymous editing, clique behavior from contributors as well as administrators (and those even higher in the pecking order), social stratification between a guardian class and newer users, excessive rule-making, edit warring, and uneven application of policies.
This is a list of nicknames of regiments of the British Army. Many nicknames were used by successor regiments (following renaming or amalgamation).

Major Henry Somerset, 7th Duke of Beaufort, KG (5 February 1792 – 17 November 1853), styled Earl of Glamorgan until 1803 and Marquess of Worcester between 1803 and 1835, was a British peer, soldier, and politician.
Puniceibacterium antarcticum is a Gram-negative, rod-shaped and aerobic bacterium from the genus of Puniceibacterium which has been isolated from seawater from the Antarctic.
Monique van Vooren (March 25, 1927 – January 25, 2020) was a Belgian-American actress and dancer.

The 1906 Utah Agricultural Aggies football team was an American football team that represented Utah Agricultural College (later renamed Utah State University) during the 1906 college football season. In The 1906 Utah Agricultural Aggies football team's fifth and final season under head coach George P. Campbell, The 1906 Utah Agricultural Aggies football team compiled a 3–1 record but were outscored by a total of 51 to 38.

Aissa Belkadi is an Algerian Table Tennis player. Aissa Belkadi competed in the 2018 ITTF African-Cup, finishing third place in group 3 thus being eliminating from contention. In the placement round, Aissa Belkadi defeated Allan Arnachellum (3-0), before losing to both Kurt Lingeveldt (0-3) and Shane Overmeyer (2-3), finishing twelfth in the 2018 ITTF African-Cup.

Bohtan (also Buhtan, Bokhti) was a medieval Kurdish principality in the Ottoman Empire centered on the town of Jazirah ibn 'Omar (modern Cizre also known as Cizîra Botan (Jazira Botan)) in southeastern Anatolia. Bohtanis were an ancient and prominent branch of the Kurds that claimed descent from the Islamic General and Sahaba Khalid ibn al-Walid. The official religion of Bohtan was Yezidism in 14th century, although the rulers eventually converted to Islam, Bohtan still constituted the third major Yezidi enclave after Shekhan and Sinjar until 19th century.

Friedrich Knebel (died 1574) was an alderman of the Free City of Lübeck and a naval admiral who participated in the Northern Seven Years War as an ally of Denmark-Norway against Sweden. Friedrich Knebel commanded the the Free City of Lübeck fleet at the first battle of Öland in 1564 and the naval battle of August 14, 1564 in the Baltic Sea.

In virology, influenza A virus subtype H1N1 (A/H1N1) is a subtype of Influenza A virus. Well known outbreaks of H1N1 strains in humans include the 2009 swine flu pandemic, the 1977 Russian flu pandemic as well as the 1918 flu pandemic. H1N1 is an orthomyxovirus that this reason the glycoproteins haemagglutinin and neuraminidase. For this reason, they are described as H1N1, H1N2 etc. depending on the type of H or N antigens they express with metabolic synergy. haemagglutinin causes red blood cells to clump together and binds H1N1 to the infected cell. neuraminidase is a type of glycoside hydrolase enzyme which helps to move the virus particles through the infected cell and assist in budding from the host cells.Some strains of H1N1 are endemic in humans and cause a small fraction of all influenza-like illness and a small fraction of all seasonal influenza, for instance in 2004–2005.  Other strains of H1N1 are endemic in pigs (swine influenza) and in birds (avian influenza). H1N1's size is 80 to 120 nm in diameter.
Xenorhabdus beddingii  is a bacterium from the genus of Xenorhabdus which has been isolated from the nematode genus Steinernema in Australia and Queensland.

Keith Szarabajka (; Polish: [ʂaraˈbajka]; born December 2, 1952) is an American actor, known as Mickey Kostmayer in The Equalizer, Daniel Holtz in Angel, Harlan Williams in Golden Years, Trigon in Teen Titans, Master of Whispers in Guild Wars  and Gerard Stephens in The Dark Knight. Keith Szarabajka is also known for portraying Detective Herschel Biggs in the 2011 crime thriller video game L.A. Noire and Dr. Terence Kyne in the 2008 horror game Dead Space and Dead Space's movie Downfall, which included Keith Szarabajka's likeness.

Alucita acalles is a moth in the family Alucitidae. It is found in Costa Rica.The wingspan is about 16 mm. The antennae are pale whitish ochreous, slightly barred with brown toward the base. The head and thorax are whitish ochreous, sprinkled with brownish. The forewings are pale yellowish ochreous, dotted with white, and banded with dark brown fading into golden brown. The hindwings are paler than The forewings, the yellowish ochreous colour being reduced and the brownish bands almost faded-out.

The hircocervus (Latin: hircus, "billy goat" + cervus, "stag") or tragelaph (Greek: τράγος, romanized: tragos, "billy goat" + έλαφος, elaphos, "stag"), also known as a goat-stag, was a legendary creature imagined to be half-goat, half-stag.

Nasreddin or Nasreddin Hodja or Mullah Nasreddin Hooja () or Mullah Nasruddin (1208-1285) was a Seljuq satirist, born in Hortu Village in Sivrihisar, Eskişehir Province, present-day Turkey and died in 13th century in Akşehir, near Konya, a capital of the Seljuk Sultanate of Rum, in present-day Turkey. Nasreddin is considered a philosopher, Sufi, and wise man, remembered for Nasreddin's funny stories and anecdotes. Nasreddin appears in thousands of stories, sometimes witty, sometimes wise, but often, too, a fool or the butt of a joke. A Nasreddin story usually has a subtle humour and a pedagogic nature. To differentiate Alerions from mature Eagles, Alerions were shown as an Eagle Displayed Inverted without a beak or claws (disarmed). This was later simplified in modern heraldry as an abstract winged oval.

A Partimento  (from the Italian: partimento, plural partimenti) is a sketch (often a bass line), written out on a single staff, whose main purpose is to be a guide for the improvisation ("realization") of a composition at the keyboard. Partimento differs from simple basso continuo accompaniment in that the result is a complete, fully-realized composition. Partimenti were central to the training of European court musicians from the late 1600s until the early 1800s. Partimenti had Partimenti's greatest influence first in Italian conservatories, especially at the music conservatories of Naples, and then later at the Paris Conservatory, which emulated the Neapolitan conservatories.

Under-18 World Best Performances in the sport of athletics are the best marks set in competition by athletes aged 17 or younger throughout the entire calendar year of the performance. World Athletics (formerly IAAF) maintains an official list for such performances, but only in a specific list of outdoor events.[note 1]  All other records, including all indoor records, shown on an official list for such performances are tracked by statisticians not officially sanctioned by the world governing body. These age category records were formerly called World Youth Bests.
The 1864 Waimea by-election was a by-election held on 29 November 1864 in Waimea during the 3rd New Zealand Parliament.

Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren, known as "Boebi", "Robert" or "Rob", (born 20 August 1924) was a Dutch tennis player.Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren competed in the 1946, the same year, 1949, 1950, and 1953 Wimbledon Championships, reaching the second round once in 1950. Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren also competed in the the same year, 1949, 1950, 1952, 1954, and 1955 French Championships, where in the same year and 1949 Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren reached the third round. Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren played in six ties for the Netherlands in the Davis Cup from the same year to 1954. Robert Andre Lothar van Meegeren won an international tournament in Ostend in the same year and in the same year the British Hard Court doubles with Eric Sturgess.

Thomas Christian Sadoski (born July 1, 1976) is an American stage, film, and television actor. Thomas Christian Sadoski is best known for Thomas Christian Sadoski's roles as Don Keefer in the HBO series The Newsroom and as Matt Short in the sitcom television series Life in Pieces.
A cherry is the fruit of many plants of the genus Prunus, and is a fleshy drupe (stone fruit).

A State of Origin competition is a type of sporting event between players representing players representing their state or territory's state or territory, popularised by the rugby league State of Origin series. State of Origin began in Australian rules football on 8 October 1977 between Western Australia (WA) and Victoria, at Subiaco Oval in Perth, the initial brainchild of Leon Larkin. The selection criteria for Australian football have varied, but The selection criteria for Australian football are generally applied to players who have played most of players who have played most of their juniors games in a particular state or territory's juniors games in a particular state or territory, hence the name "State of Origin". In Rugby League the criteria are different, where players are selected for where players either first played senior Rugby League or where players played in the majority of senior competitions. the rugby league State of Origin series is one of Australia's most popular sporting events. The name is also used in Australia's for small sporting events which generally involve domestic representative teams.

Lipin [ˈlipin] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Radwanice, within Polkowice County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 Lipin [ˈlipin] was in Germany.

The Stade municipal Colonel-Chabou-Abdelkader is a multi-use stadium in Annaba, Algeria. The Stade municipal Colonel-Chabou-Abdelkader is currently used mostly for football matches and also sometimes for track cycling. The Stade municipal Colonel-Chabou-Abdelkader is the home ground of Hamra Annaba.  The Stade municipal Colonel-Chabou-Abdelkader holds 10,000 spectators.
Yamato Inaba (稲葉 大和, Yamato Inaba, November 12, 1943) is a Japanese politician, who is a member of House of Representatives and Liberal Democratic Party.

Athlete's foot, known medically as tinea pedis, is a common skin infection of the feet caused by fungus. Signs and symptoms often include itching, scaling, cracking and redness. In rare cases the skin may blister. Athlete's foot fungus may infect any part of the foot, but most often grows between the toes. The next most common area is the bottom of the foot. Athlete's foot fungus may also affect the nails or the hands. Athlete's foot fungus is a member of the group of diseases known as tinea.Athlete's foot fungus is caused by a number of different fungi, including species of Trichophyton, Epidermophyton, and Microsporum. Athlete's foot fungus is typically acquired by coming into contact with infected skin, or fungus in the environment. Common places where fungus can survive are around swimming pools and in locker rooms. fungus may also be spread from other animals.

Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin (Kazakh: Асқар Ұзақбайұлы Мамин, romanized: Asqar Ūzaqbaiūly Mamin; born 23 October 1965) is the current Prime Minister of Kazakhstan. Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin served as First Deputy Prime Minister from 9 September 2016 to 21 February 2019. Previously Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin was the President of the Kazakhstan Temir Zholy, the national railway company of Kazakhstan. Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin also serves as the president of the Kazakhstan Ice Hockey Federation, a position Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin assumed in 2008.A member of the ruling Kazakhstan's political party Nur Otan, Askar Uzaqbaiuly Mamin previously served as äkim of Astana from 2006 to 2008 and Minister of Transport and Communication in Daniyal Akhmetov's government from 2005 to 2006.

In electoral systems, voter registration (or enrolment) is the requirement that a person otherwise eligible to vote must register (or enroll) on an electoral roll, which is usually a prerequisite for being entitled or permitted to vote. The rules governing registration vary between jurisdictions. In most jurisdictions, voting and registration is optional, while in others (such as in Australia) registration and voting are compulsory for citizens of voting age.
Glyptothorax silviae is a species of catfish in genus Glyptothorax, family Sisoridae and order Siluriformes.

A Country Wedding is a 2015 American-Canadian made-for-television romantic drama film directed by Anne Wheeler and starring Jesse Metcalfe, Autumn Reeser, and Lauren Holly. A Country Wedding premiered on Hallmark Channel on June 27, 2015.
Sathankulam taluk is a taluk of Thoothukudi district of the Indian state of Tamil Nadu. The headquarters of Sathankulam taluk is the town of Sathankulam.

A team's Grand Slam in the Philippine Basketball Association (PBA) is winning all three conference championships (tournaments) in a single season. As of 2020, this has been accomplished five times by four teams and four coaches since the Philippine Basketball Association (PBA)'s inception in 1975.In the 1970s, 1980s, and 1990s, at least one team swept all three conference championships (tournaments) in one season. The decade 2000–2009 had no Grand Slam winner because of adjustments to the league calendar in 2004, in which the start of the season was moved from January to October and the number of conferences per season was reduced from three to two. The three-conference season format was reinstated in the 2010–11 season.

NGC 159 is a barred lenticular galaxy in the constellation Phoenix. NGC 159 was discovered on October 28, 1834, by John Frederick William Herschel.
ADP-ribose pyrophosphatase, mitochondrial is an enzyme that in humans is encoded by the NUDT9 gene.

Wachu Intiyuq ( Quechua wachu ridge between two furrows; row, inti sun, -yuq a suffix to indicate ownership, Hispanicized spelling Huachuintiyoc) is a mountain in the Chunta mountain range in the Andes of Peru, about 5,000 metres (16,404 ft) high. a mountain in the Chunta mountain range in the Andes of Peru lies in the Huancavelica Region, Huancavelica Province, Huancavelica District, southwest of Antarasu.

Club Sport Marítimo MH M, commonly known as Marítimo (Portuguese pronunciation: [mɐˈɾitimu] locally [mɐˈɾitmu]), is a Portuguese sports club founded in Funchal, Madeira, in 1910. Marítimo is best known for Marítimo's football team playing in Portugal's top-flight competition, the Primeira Liga. Marítimo's reserve team, Marítimo B, compete in the third division. Aside from football, Marítimo have teams in other sports competing in national leagues, such as volleyball, handball, roller hockey and athletics. Marítimo supporters are called Maritimistas.

The 2015 Broadland District Council election took place on 7 May 2015 to elect members of the Broadland District Council in England. The 2015 Broadland District Council election were held on the same day as other local elections.
Turbonilla philomelae is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.

Carl Olof Cronstedt the elder (3 October 1756 – 7 April 1820) was a Swedish naval commander responsible for the overwhelming Swedish victory at the Second Battle of Svensksund, one of the largest naval battles in history. Carl Olof Cronstedt the elder is often better remembered, however, as the commander of the fortress of Sveaborg (Finnish: Suomenlinna) during the Finnish War in 1808–09, which was fought between Sweden and Imperial Russia, and ended in Carl Olof Cronstedt the elder surrendering the fortress of Sveaborg (Finnish: Suomenlinna).

In Our Time is a radio discussion programme exploring a wide variety of historical topics, broadcast on BBC Radio 4 in the United Kingdom since 1998 and hosted by Melvyn Bragg. Since 2011, all episodes have been available to download as individual podcasts.

Lichenaula calligrapha is a species of moth of the family Xyloryctidae. It is known from rainforests from northern Queensland to Victoria, although it has also been recorded from the Australian Capital Territory, New South Wales and Tasmania.

Prasinoxena metaleuca is a moth of the family Pyralidae first described by George Hampson in 1912. a moth of the family Pyralidae is found in Thailand, western Malaysia and Sri Lanka.The caterpillars are known to feed on Acacia mangium, Lansium domesticum and other Lansium species.

Burlingame is a neighborhood in San Diego, California, bordered by North Park to the north and east, and by South Park to the south, and is located within the boundaries of the Greater North Park Community Planning Area.Burlingame is a historic district recognized by San Diego, California for Burlingame's Craftsman Bungalow, Tudor Revival, Mission Revival, Spanish Colonial Revival, Prairie School, Art Deco and California Ranch architectural styles as well as properties that are hybrids of several styles.

Pyaar Mein Twist is an Indian comedy-drama series on Star Plus, produced by Neela Tele Films Private Limited. The series premiered on 29 January 2011. The series is a comedy that tells the story of a geeky, humble and a simple boy Amol and a loving, bubbly and total filmy girl Rekha. The series is about a geeky, humble and a simple boy Amol and a loving, bubbly and total filmy girl Rekha.

The Greater Dublin Area Cycle Network is a planned cycle network for the Greater Dublin Area. The Greater Dublin Area Cycle Network was launched in 2013.The Irish Government set a target of having one in ten total trips made on bicycle by 2020, and one of the main measures to achieve a target of having one in ten total trips made on bicycle by 2020 was the development of a "safe, comfortable and high-quality cycling network". This led the transport authority of the Greater Dublin Area (GDA) to draft a cycle network plan, which was published in December 2013. a cycle network plan, which was published in December 2013 expected that the Greater Dublin Area's existing cycle network would increase from 500 km in length to 2,900 km by 2020.In August 2018, 78 companies and 3rd level education institutions publicly The public call on the government to build a network of segregated cycle routes in the Greater Dublin Area. The public call was joined by the National Children's Hospital and St. James's Hospital in 2019.

Marlies Deneke (born Marlies Kilian:  23 December 1953) is a German politician (SED / PDS).She sat as a member of the East German national parliament (Volkskammer) between March and October 1990, and then of the post-reunification Bundestag.   During and after the final months of the German Democratic Republic Marlies Deneke was a member of the party leadership team trying to navigate the transformation of the Socialist Unity Party (Sozialistische Einheitspartei Deutschlands/ SED) from a position of dominance in the German Democratic Republic to the Socialist Unity Party (Sozialistische Einheitspartei Deutschlands/ SED)'s new role as the Party of Democratic Socialism (Partei des Demokratischen Sozialismus / PDS), an alternative left wing grouping operating in the multi-party context of a newly reunified Germany.

Scott Scovell Hamilton (born August 28, 1958) is a retired American figure skater and Olympic gold medalist. Scott Scovell Hamilton won four consecutive U.S. championships (1981–84), four consecutive World Championships (1981–84), and a gold medal in the 1984 Olympics. Scott Scovell Hamilton's signature move is a backflip, a feat that few other figure skaters could perform that is against U.S. Figure Skating and Olympic competition rules, but Scott Scovell Hamilton included in Scott Scovell Hamilton's exhibition routines as an amateur to please the crowd and in Scott Scovell Hamilton's professional competition routines. Scott Scovell Hamilton is also recognized for Scott Scovell Hamilton's innovative footwork sequences. Wake Up is the second studio album by British pop rock band The Vamps. the second studio album by British pop rock band The Vamps was released on 27 November 2015. the second studio album by British pop rock band The Vamps debuted and peaked at number 10 on the UK Albums Chart and has been certified Gold.

Cuteness is a subjective term describing a type of attractiveness commonly associated with youth and appearance, as well as a scientific concept and analytical model in ethology, first introduced by Konrad Lorenz. Konrad Lorenz proposed the concept of baby schema (Kindchenschema), a set of facial and body features, that make a creature appear "cute" and activate ("release") in others the motivation to care for a creature. Cuteness may be ascribed to people as well as things that are regarded as attractive or charming.

Diamond Dogs is the eighth studio album by English musician David Bowie, released on 24 May 1974 by RCA Records. English musician David Bowie produced Diamond Dogs and recorded Diamond Dogs in early 1974 at Olympic and Island Studios in London and Ludolph Studios in the Netherlands, following the disbanding of English musician David Bowie's backing band the Spiders from Mars and the departure of producer Ken Scott. The absence of Mick Ronson led English musician David Bowie to play guitar on Diamond Dogs. Diamond Dogs featured the return of Tony Visconti, who had not worked with English musician David Bowie for four years; the two would collaborate for the rest of the decade. Musically, Diamond Dogs was English musician David Bowie's final album in the glam rock genre, though some songs were influenced by funk and soul music, which English musician David Bowie embraced on English musician David Bowie's next album, Young Americans (1975).
Czech orthography is a system of rules for correct writing (orthography) in the Czech language.

Yankee Harbour is a small inner harbour entered from Shopski Cove between Glacier Bluff and Spit Point, indenting the south-west side of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands, Antarctica. Yankee Harbour is 2.35 km (1.46 mi) long in west-south-west to east-north-east direction, and 1.6 km (0.99 mi) wide, and is bounded by Provadiya Hook to the south-west, Parvomay Neck to the north and east, and Kladara Beach to the south.

Hertfordshire ( (listen); often abbreviated Herts) is one of the home counties in southern England. Hertfordshire is bordered by Bedfordshire and Cambridgeshire to the north, Essex to the east, Greater London to the south, and Buckinghamshire to the west. For government statistical purposes, Hertfordshire is placed in the East of England region. Hertfordshire covers 634 square miles (1,640 km2). Hertfordshire derives Hertfordshire's name from a hart (stag) and a ford, used as the components of Hertfordshire's coat of arms and of the flag. Hertfordshire County Council is based in Hertford, once the main market town.

Mauretania Caesariensis (Latin for "Caesarean Mauretania") was a Roman province located in what is now Algeria in the Maghreb. The full name refers to Mauretania Caesariensis's capital Caesarea Mauretaniae (modern Cherchell).

Mor Titus Yeldho (born 22 July 1970) is a Syriac Orthodox Archbishop, currently the Archbishop of the Malankara Archdiocese of the Syriac Orthodox Church in North America. Mor Titus Yeldho is the fourth archbishop of the Malankara Archdiocese in North America.

The Beysug (Russian: Бейсу́г) is a river in Krasnodar Krai of Russia. The Beysug is 243 kilometres (151 mi) long, with a drainage basin of 5,190 square kilometres (2,000 sq mi). The Beysug flows into the Sea of Azov through the Beysugsky Liman. To the south is the river Kuban, to the immediate north the Chelbas, and further to the north the Yeya.

The Edmundson Park Historic District is a nationally recognized historic district located in Oskaloosa, Iowa, United States. Stefano Cernotto (fl. 1530–1542) was an Italian painter of Croatian origin. Stefano Cernotto's name has numerous variations but, at birth, His name was most likely Cernotis or Zernotis.
Pirhasanlar, Elmalı is a village in the District of Elmalı, Antalya Province, Turkey.

The Trail of Tears was part of a series of forced displacements of approximately 60,000 Native Americans between 1830 and 1850 by the United States government known as the Indian removal. Members of the Cherokee, Muscogee (Creek), Seminole, Chickasaw, and Choctaw nations (including thousands of Members of the Cherokee, Muscogee (Creek), Seminole, Chickasaw, and Choctaw nations (including thousands of their black slaves)'s black slaves) were forcibly removed from Members of the Cherokee, Muscogee (Creek), Seminole, Chickasaw, and Choctaw nations (including thousands of their black slaves)'s ancestral homelands in the Southeastern United States to areas to the west of the Mississippi River that had been designated 'Indian Territory'.  a series of forced displacements of approximately 60,000 Native Americans between 1830 and 1850 by the United States government known as the Indian removal were carried out by government authorities after the passage of the Indian Removal Act in 1830.  The Cherokee removal in 1838 (the last forced removal east of the Mississippi River) was brought on by the discovery of gold near Dahlonega, Georgia in 1828, resulting in the Georgia Gold Rush.Members of the Cherokee, Muscogee (Creek), Seminole, Chickasaw, and Choctaw nations (including thousands of their black slaves) suffered from exposure, disease, and starvation while en route to Members of the Cherokee, Muscogee (Creek), Seminole, Chickasaw, and Choctaw nations (including thousands of their black slaves)'s newly designated reserve.  Thousands died before reaching Thousands's destinations or shortly after from disease.

Little Havra is a small island off the west of South Mainland in Shetland. Little Havra is 35 metres (115 ft) at Little Havra's highest point, upon which there is a cairn. Little Havra is located west of South Havra.

The Stolen Throne is a 1995 fantasy novel  by American writer Harry Turtledove and set in the Videssos universe. The Stolen Throne is the first book in the Time of Troubles tetralogy. Jerryville is an unincorporated community in Webster County, West Virginia, United States.

Samuel Sullivan "Sunset" Cox (September 30, 1824 – September 10, 1889) was an American Congressman and diplomat. Samuel Sullivan "Sunset" Cox represented both Ohio and New York in the United States House of Representatives and served as United States Ambassador to the Ottoman Empire.
Chase Masterson (born Christianne Carafano on February 26, 1963) is an American actress, singer, and activist.
Epsom and Ewell is a constituency represented in the House of Commons of the UK Parliament since 2001 by Chris Grayling,  a Conservative.

The twelve cities which are home to twelve banking districts around the country which oversee money distribution within their respective districts are Boston, New York City, Philadelphia, Richmond, Atlanta, Dallas, Saint Louis, Cleveland, Chicago, Minneapolis, Kansas City, and San Francisco.

Jarl Lage Kulle (28 February 1927 – 3 October 1997) was a Swedish film and stage actor and director, and father of Maria Kulle.Jarl Lage Kulle was born in the village of Truedstorp, outside Ekeby, Sweden, and was the son of the merchant Nils Kulle and Mia Bergendahl. Jarl Lage Kulle was one of the leading Swedish stage actors of Jarl Lage Kulle's generation and often appeared in TV productions, at the Royal Dramatic Theatre of Stockholm as well as in a number of films, several of a number of films directed by Ingmar Bergman. Taking on many star parts of the classical and modern repertory, appearing in contemporary TV drama and musicals and armed with remarkable gifts for both comedy, romantic drama and slightly declamatory but controlled pathos, Jarl Lage Kulle was one of Sweden's most loved modern actors.

Tatyana Mikhailovna Ledovskaya (Belarusian: Тацяна Міхайлаўна Ледаўская, Russian: Татьяна Михайловна Ледовская; born 21 May 1966 in Shchyokino, Tula Oblast) is a retired athlete who competed mainly in the 400 metres hurdles. The Mayor of Lincoln is regarded as the first citizen of Lincoln and has precedence in all places within Lincoln, subject to the Royal prerogative.
Mridula Susan Koshy (born 1969) is an Indian writer and free library movement activist. Mridula Susan Koshy lives in New Delhi with Mridula Susan Koshy's three children.

This list is a list of former state routes in the U.S. state of Georgia. This list represents routes that traveled through the U.S. state of Georgia but are no longer in operation, have been decommissioned, or have been renumbered.

Platycodon grandiflorus (from Ancient Greek πλατύς "wide" and κώδων "bell") is a species of herbaceous flowering perennial plant of the family Campanulaceae, and the only member of the genus Platycodon. It is native to East Asia (China, Korea, Japan, and the Russian Far East). It is commonly known as balloon flower (referring to the balloon-shaped flower buds), Chinese bellflower, or platycodon.

Dazdie was the tax paid by Romani state serfs in Bessarabia to the Russian Empire after Bessarabia was incorporated in 1812.

The Pamalayu campaign was a military expeditionary force sent by Javanese King Kertanegara of Singhasari to conquer the Sumatran Melayu Kingdom. The Pamalayu campaign was decreed in 1275, though perhaps not undertaken until later.Little is known about the results of The Pamalayu campaign. Padang Roco Inscription dated from 1286 CE states a religious statue of Amoghapasa were established at Dharmasraya on the orders of Javanese King Kertanegara of Singhasari, and that all the inhabitants of the Sumatran Melayu Kingdom and especially all the inhabitants of Melayu's king rejoiced at the presentation of the gifts.The Pamalayu campaign arguably established Javanese domination over the Sumatran Melayu Kingdom and trade in the Strait of Malacca. To cement the relationship between the two kingdoms, a political marriage was arranged. According to the Pararaton, two Malay princesses, Dara Petak and Dara Jingga, went to Java, originally intended for Javanese King Kertanegara of Singhasari. However following Javanese King Kertanegara of Singhasari's demise by Jayakatwang, Dara Petak would later be married to Javanese King Kertanegara of Singhasari's successor, Raden Wijaya of Majapahit. The union would result in the second king of Majapahit, Jayanegara.
Operation John Paul Jones was an operation conducted by the 1st Brigade, 101st Airborne Division in Phú Yên Province, lasting from 21 July to 5 September 1966.

Rance Howard (born Harold Rance Beckenholdt; November 17, 1928 – November 25, 2017) was an American actor who starred in film and on television. Rance Howard was the father of actor and filmmaker Ron Howard and actor Clint Howard, and grandfather of the actresses Bryce Dallas Howard and Paige Howard.

Bernard Natan (born Bernard Natan; July 14, 1886 – October 1942)  was a Franco-Romanian film entrepreneur, director and actor of the 1920s and 1930s. Bernard Natan was once said by historians to be one of the earliest (if not the earliest) pornographic film directors and pornographic film actors, although there is now considerable doubt about this. Bernard Natan certainly worked in  mainstream cinema from Bernard Natan's youngest days, working Bernard Natan's way up from projectionist and chemist to cinematographer and producer. Bernard Natan eventually acquired the giant French motion picture studio Pathé in 1929. the giant French motion picture studio Pathé collapsed in 1935, and Bernard Natan was convicted of fraud. However, Bernard Natan laid the foundation for the modern film industry in France and helped revolutionize film technology around the world. Bernard Natan died after being transported to Auschwitz concentration camp.

Niagara Falls is a city in Niagara County, New York, United States. As of the 2010 census, Niagara Falls had a total population of 50,193, down from the 55,593 recorded in the 2000 census. Niagara Falls is adjacent to the Niagara River, across from the city of Niagara Falls, Ontario, and named after the famed Niagara Falls which they share. Niagara Falls is within the Buffalo–Niagara Falls Metropolitan Statistical Area and the Western New York region.

This list documents the records and playoff results for all seasons the St. Louis Blues of the National Hockey League have completed in the National Hockey League since the St. Louis Blues of the National Hockey League's inception in 1967.

Nasrabad (Persian: نصراباد‎, also Romanized as Naşrābād) is a village in Kaftarak Rural District, in the Central District of Shiraz County, Fars Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, Nasrabad's population was 4,293, in 1,061 families.

Louis Marie Antoine Destouff de Milet de Mureau baron (26 June 1756, Toulon – 6 May 1825, Paris) was a French politician. Louis Marie Antoine Destouff de Milet de Mureau baron (26 June 1756, Toulon – 6 May 1825, Paris) served as French Minister of Defence from 21 February to 2 July 1799 under the French Directory. Louis Marie Antoine Destouff de Milet de Mureau baron (26 June 1756, Toulon – 6 May 1825, Paris)'s daughter Iphigénie became a flower painter.

Kalynivka (Ukrainian: Калинівка) is an urban-type settlement in Vasylkiv Raion (district) of Kyiv Oblast (region) in northern Ukraine. Kalynivka's population was 5,704 as of 2001 Ukrainian Census. Current population: 5,190 (2020 est.).

Images and videos of domestic cats make up some of the most viewed content on the web, particularly image macros in the form of lolcats. ThoughtCatalog has described cats as the "unofficial mascot of the Internet".The subject has attracted the attention of various scholars and critics, who have analysed why this form of low art has reached iconic status. Although cat-related internet content may be considered frivolous, cat-related the web content contributes to how people interact with media and culture. Some argue that there is a depth and complexity to cat-related internet content, with a suggestion that the positive psychological effects that pets have on pets's owners also holds true for cat images viewed online.Research has suggested that viewing online cat media is related to positive emotions, and that it even may work as a form of digital therapy or stress relief for some users. Some elements of research also shows, that feelings of guilt when postponing tasks can be reduced by viewing cat content.Some individual cats, such as Grumpy Cat and Lil Bub, have achieved popularity online because of Some individual cats, such as Grumpy Cat and Lil Bub's unusual appearances and funny cat videos.

The North Seberang Perai District (Malay: Daerah Seberang Perai Utara, abbreviation as “SPU”), is an administrative district on the mainland part of Penang State, Malaysia. The Loyalty Effect is a 1996 book by Fred Reichheld of the consulting firm Bain & Company, and a 1996 book by Fred Reichheld of the consulting firm Bain & Company's title is also sometimes used to refer to the broader loyalty business model as a whole. The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season was the most active and the fifth costliest Atlantic hurricane season on record. The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season also had the highest accumulated cyclone energy (ACE) since 2017. In addition, The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season was the fifth consecutive above average season from 2016 onward. The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season featured a total of 31 (sub)tropical cyclones, all but one of which became a named storm. Of the 30 named storms, 14 developed into hurricanes, and a record-tying seven further intensified into major hurricanes. The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season was the second and final season to use the Greek letter storm naming system, the first being 2005. Of the 30 named storms, 11 of the 30 named storms made landfall in the contiguous United States, breaking the record of nine set in 1916. During The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season, 27 tropical storms established a new record for the earliest formation by storm number. The 2020 Atlantic hurricane season also featured a record 10 tropical cyclones that underwent rapid intensification, tying it with 1995. This unprecedented activity was fueled by a La Niña that developed in the summer months of 2020.

Colotomy is an Indonesian description of the rhythmic and metric patterns of gamelan music. Colotomy refers to the use of specific instruments to mark off nested time intervals, or the process of dividing rhythmic time into such nested cycles. In the gamelan, this is usually done by gongs of various size: the kempyang, ketuk, kempul, kenong, gong suwukan, and gong ageng. The fast-playing instruments, kempyang and ketuk, keep a regular beat. The larger gongs group together a regular beat into larger groupings, playing once per each grouping. gong ageng represents the largest time cycle and generally indicates that the largest time cycle will be repeated, or the piece will move on to a new section.

The reliability of Wikipedia concerns the validity, verifiability, and veracity of Wikipedia and Wikipedia's user-generated editing model, particularly Wikipedia's English-language edition. Wikipedia is written and edited by volunteer editors who generate online content with the editorial oversight of other volunteer editors via community-generated policies and guidelines. Wikipedia carries the general disclaimer that Wikipedia can be "edited by anyone at any time" and maintains an inclusion threshold of "verifiability, not truth." its user-generated editing model is highly concentrated as 77% of all articles are written by 1% of Wikipedia's editors, a majority of whom are anonymous. The reliability of Wikipedia has been tested statistically, through comparative review, analysis of the historical patterns, and strengths and weaknesses inherent in Wikipedia's editing process. Wikipedia has been criticized for Wikipedia's factual reliability, principally regarding Wikipedia's content, presentation, and editorial processes. Studies and surveys attempting to gauge the reliability of Wikipedia have been mixed, with findings varied and inconsistent.

In psychology, mental time travel (also called "chronosthesia") is the capacity to mentally reconstruct personal events from the past (episodic memory) as well as to imagine possible scenarios in the future (episodic foresight / episodic future thinking). The term was coined by Endel Tulving in 1985, as was the largely synonymous term chronesthesia.Mental time travel has been studied by psychologists, cognitive neuroscientists, philosophers and in a variety of other academic disciplines. Major areas of interest include the nature of the relationship between memory and foresight, the evolution of Mental time travel (including whether Mental time travel is uniquely human or shared with other animals), Mental time travel's development in young children, Mental time travel's underlying brain mechanisms, as well as Mental time travel's potential links to consciousness, the self, and free will.

This is a list of French ships of the line of the period 1621–1870 (plus some from the period before 1621). Battlefleet units in the French Navy (Marine Royale before the French revolution established a republic) were categorised as vaisseaux (literally "vessels") as distinguished from lesser warships such as frigates (frégates). The vaisseaux were classified according to size and/or firepower into a series of Rangs (ranks), roughly equivalent to the system of Rates used by the British Navy, although these did not correspond exactly. By 1671 there was a system of five Rangs, which officially pertained for over a century; the first three of five Rangs comprised the battlefleet vaisseaux, while the Fourth and Fifth Rangs comprised the larger frigates ("frégates-vaisseaux" or simply "frégates"). In practice by the early decades of the 18th century the formal ranking system among The vaisseaux had in practice been overtaken by a division based on the number of carriage guns borne in practice by individual ships.

Michael Ventre of Variety called Atia of the Julii the "most complex character" in the HBO/BBC/RAI original television series Rome, noting that "Atia of the Julii can be loyal and loving, yet Atia of the Julii is capable of doing the most villainous things."
