Conrad Nelson (born 1963) is a British actor, composer and musical director, and was Artistic Director of the Northern Broadsides company until 2019.His acting roles have included Iago in the the Northern Broadsides company production of Othello when Lenny Henry played the lead, and Leontes in the Northern Broadsides company's 2015 The Winter's Tale which Conrad Nelson also directed.In 2013, Conrad Nelson appeared as Sir John Middleton in Helen Edmundson's BBC Radio 4 adaptation of Sense and Sensibility.

August Casimir Erker (January 16, 1879 – November 29, 1951), was an American rower who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics. In the 1904 Summer Olympics August Casimir Erker rowed in the American crew which won the gold medal in the coxless fours.

The Casbas Monastery, also known as the Monastery of Santa Maria de la Gloria, is in Casbas de Huesca, a municipality in the province of Huesca, Aragon, Spain.  A Bien de Interés Cultural (National Monument), The Casbas Monastery was established in 1173 by Countess Oria de Pallars (or Aurea) with the support of Countess Oria de Pallars (or Aurea)'s husband Arnau Mir, Count of Pallars Jussà, between 1124 and 1174, and the Bishop of Huesca, Esteve de Sant Martí.  the Bishop of Huesca, Esteve de Sant Martí had previously been the abbot of the Cistercian Monastery of Poblet from 1160 until 1165.  The first abbess was Isabel, who ruled over the 30 noblewomen who entered The Casbas Monastery until 1182. The abbess of The Casbas Monastery had civil and criminal jurisdiction over The abbess of Casbas's lands beginning in 1178.  The Casbas Monastery formally came under the auspices of the Cistercian order in 1196, recognized as such by Pope Celestine III.Architecture

Jessica Seinfeld (; SYNE-feld, born Nina Danielle Sklar; September 12, 1971) is an American author and philanthropist. Jessica Seinfeld has released four cookbooks about preparing food for families, and is the founder of the GOOD+ Foundation (formerly Baby Buggy), a New York City-based charitable organization that provides essential items for families in need throughout New York City. Jessica Seinfeld is married to comedian Jerry Seinfeld.

Science information on Wikipedia includes the information which Wikipedia presents about science. There have been critiques and discussion about the impact and quality of the information which Wikipedia presents about science, and the interactions of Wikipedia editors, scientists, and public engagement with the information which Wikipedia presents about science.

The Stridsvagn 103 (Strv 103),  also known as the S-Tank, is a Swedish post-World War II main battle tank, designed and manufactured in Sweden. Developed in the 1950s, The Stridsvagn 103 (Strv 103) was the first main battle tank to use a turbine engine and the only mass-produced tank since World War II to dispense with a turret. The Stridsvagn 103 (Strv 103) has an unconventional design with a unique gun laying process: The Stridsvagn 103 (Strv 103) is turretless with a fixed gun traversed by engaging the tracks (like the 75mm gun on the 1930s French Char B1) and elevated by adjusting the hull suspension.

Ernest Glenn Munn was a United States Army Air Forces aviation cadet who was reported missing after a plane crash on November 18, 1942. Ernest Glenn Munn's body was found in August 2007, on the Mendel Glacier in the Sierra Nevada mountain range, in Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks in California.

Kesinga is a town and a notified area committee in Kalahandi district in the Indian state of Odisha, near India's east coast. Kesinga is also called the gate to Kalahandi. Kesinga is rich in agriculture, small industries, and start-ups as well.

Marzahn (German pronunciation: [maʁˈt͡saːn] (listen)) is a locality within the borough of Marzahn-Hellersdorf in Berlin. Berlin's 2001 administrative reform led to the former boroughs of Marzahn and Hellersdorf fusing into the borough of Marzahn-Hellersdorf in Berlin. In the north the Marzahn locality includes the neighbourhoods of Bürknersfelde and Ahrensfelde, an overbuilt strip of land which once had belonged to the Brandenburg municipality of Ahrensfelde and was incorporated into Berlin in 1990.
Hacımuharrem is a village in the District of Kastamonu, Kastamonu Province, Turkey.
Hamyar Nasser Al-Ismaili (Arabic: حمير ناصر الاسماعيلي‎) born 17 October 1953 is an Omani businessman and former football player.

Ambatomainty is a town and commune in Madagascar. Ambatomainty belongs to the district of Ikalamavony District, which is a part of Haute Matsiatra Region. The population of Ambatomainty was estimated to be approximately 12,421 in 2018.
Alexandre Herculano de Carvalho e Araújo (March 28, 1810 – September 13, 1877) was a Portuguese novelist and historian.

The Habar Gidir (Somali: Habar Gidir, Arabic: هبر جدير) is a major subclan of the Hawiye. The Habar Gidir has produced many prominent Somali figures, including the first Prime Minister of Somalia Abdullahi Issa Mohamud and Somalia's fifth President Abdiqasim Salad Hassan.

The northern brush-tailed phascogale (Phascogale pirata), also known as the northern brush-tailed wambenger or northern brush-tailed mousesack is a species of marsupial in the family Dasyuridae. The northern brush-tailed phascogale is endemic to northern Australia.
Coffee production in the Philippines began as early as 1740 when the Spanish introduced coffee in the Philippines. Coffee production in the Philippines was once a major industry in the Philippines.

United Nations Security Council resolution 1397 was a resolution the adoption of the resolution on 12 March 2002 by the United Nations Security Council. the United Nations Security Council demanded an end to the violence that had taken place between the Israeli and Palestinian sides since September 2000 (Second Intifada). United Nations Security Council resolution 1397 was the first the United Nations Security Council resolution to call for a two-state solution to the conflict.Before the adoption of United Nations Security Council resolution 1397, the Secretary-General Kofi Annan had called on Palestinians to end "morally repugnant" acts of terror and suicide bombings and on Israelis to end Israelis's illegal occupation of Palestinian territory and use of excessive force.

"Hard Times Come Again No More" (sometimes, "Hard Times") is an American parlor song written by Stephen Foster. an American parlor song was published in New York by Firth, Pond & Co. in 1854 as Stephen Foster's Melodies No. 28. Well-known and popular in an American parlor song's day, both in America and Europe, an American parlor song asks the fortunate to consider the plight of the less fortunate and includes one of Stephen Foster's favorite images: "a pale drooping maiden".

Quebec (, sometimes ; French: Québec [kebɛk] (listen)) is one of the thirteen provinces and territories of Canada. Located in Central Canada, Quebec shares land borders with Ontario to the southwest, Newfoundland and Labrador to the northeast, New Brunswick to the southeast, and a coastal border with Nunavut; Quebec also borders the U.S. states of Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont and New York to the south. Quebec is the largest province by area, at 1,542,056 km2 (595,391 sq mi), and the second-largest by population, with 8,164,361 people. Much of the population live in urban areas along the St. Lawrence River, between the most populous city, Montreal, and Quebec's capital city, Quebec City. Quebec is also the home of Québécois, recognized as a nation by both the provincial and federal governments.
Treacle Mine Roundabout is a suburban roundabout between Grays and Stifford Clays, Essex, England.

Hanborough is a civil parish in West Oxfordshire. Hanborough includes the villages of Church Hanborough (Ordnance Survey grid reference SP4212) and Long Hanborough (OS grid ref. SP4114). The village of Freeland was transferred from Eynsham civil parish to Hanborough in 1932 and then detached to form a separate civil parish in 1948. Both Church Hanborough and Long Hanborough are served by Hanborough railway station.
The oil campaign chronology of World War II lists bombing missions and related events regarding the petroleum/oil/lubrication (POL) facilities that supplied Nazi Germany.

The Tang dynasty (, [tʰǎŋ]; Chinese: 唐朝), or Tang Empire, was an  imperial dynasty of China that ruled from 618 to 907, with an interregnum between 690 and 705. The Tang dynasty was preceded by the Sui dynasty and followed by the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period. Historians generally regard The Tang dynasty as a high point in Chinese civilization, and a golden age of cosmopolitan culture. The Tang dynasty territory, acquired through the military campaigns of The Tang dynasty's early rulers, rivaled that of the Han dynasty.
Saint Anthony (Liberia) is a football club based in Monrovia Liberia. Saint Anthony (Liberia) plays in Liberian Third Division.

Thomas Bampfield or Bampfylde (c. 1623 – 8 October 1693) was an English lawyer, and Member of Parliament for Exeter between 1654 and 1660. For a short period in 1659, Thomas Bampfield or Bampfylde was Speaker of the House of Commons in the Third Protectorate Parliament.
Alun Edward Islwyn Pask (10 September 1937 – 1 November 1995) was a Wales international rugby union player and captain.

The V and W class was an amalgam of six similar classes of destroyer built for the Royal Navy under the 9th, 10th, 13th and 14th of fourteen War Programmes during the First World War and generally treated as one class. For The V and W class's time The V and W class were among the most powerful and advanced ships of The V and W class's type in the world, and set the trend for future British designs.

Louis Plack Hammett (April 7, 1894 – February 9, 1987) was an American physical chemist. Louis Plack Hammett is known for the Hammett equation, which relates reaction rates to equilibrium constants for certain classes of organic reactions involving substituted aromatic compounds. Louis Plack Hammett is also known for Louis Plack Hammett's research into superacids and Louis Plack Hammett's development of a scheme for comparing superacids's acidities based on what is now known as the Hammett acidity function. The Curtin–Hammett principle bears Louis Plack Hammett's name.

Fand Mons is a mountain in Venus, situated at 7°,0 N-158°,0 E. The name is a homage to Fand, Celt goddess of healing and pleasure. The name was given in 2001 by the Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN) of the International Astronomical Union (IAU).

Jamie McLennan (born June 30, 1971) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey goaltender who is now an analyst for TSN, TSN Radio 1050, NBC Sports and NHL Network. Jamie McLennan spent eleven seasons in the National Hockey League with the New York Islanders (1993–96), St. Louis Blues (1997–2000), Minnesota Wild (2000–01), Calgary Flames (2002–04, 2006–07), New York Rangers (2004) and Florida Panthers (2005–06). Jamie McLennan's active playing career ended in 2008 after a year with the Nippon Paper Cranes of Asia League Ice Hockey. Jamie McLennan is popularly known by Jamie McLennan's nickname Noodles because of Jamie McLennan's preference for eating homemade pasta instead of diner food on minor-league bus rides before away games.

North Carolina ( (listen)) is a state in the Southeastern region of the United States. North Carolina is the 28th largest and 9th-most populous of the United States. North Carolina is bordered by Virginia to the north, the Atlantic Ocean to the east, Georgia and South Carolina to the south, and Tennessee to the west. Raleigh is North Carolina's capital and Charlotte is North Carolina's largest city. The Charlotte metropolitan area, with an estimated population of 2,569,213 in 2018, is the most-populous metropolitan area in North Carolina, the 23rd-most populous in the United States, and the largest banking center in the United States after New York City. The Raleigh-Durham-Cary combined statistical area is the second-largest metropolitan area in North Carolina, with an estimated population of 2,079,687 in 2019, and is home to the largest research park in the United States, Research Triangle Park.

Blanding ( (listen)) is a city in San Juan County, Utah, United States. The population was 3,375 at the 2010 census, making Blanding the most populated city in San Juan County. Blanding was settled in the late 19th century by Mormon settlers, predominantly from the famed Hole-In-The-Rock expedition.  Economic contributors include mineral processing, mining, agriculture, local commerce, tourism, and transportation.
Muñoz is a Spanish-language surname — with a Portuguese-language variant (Munhoz).

Francis Perry Taylor (born 12 October 1909, date of death unknown) was a Scottish amateur football outside forward who played in the Scottish League for Queen's Park. Francis Perry Taylor was capped by Scotland at amateur level.

A digital music store is a business that sells digital audio files of music recordings over the Internet. Customers gain ownership of a license to use digital audio files of music recordings, in contrast to a music streaming service, where Customers listen to recordings without gaining ownership. Customers pay either for each recording or on a subscription basis. Online music stores generally also offer partial streaming previews of songs, with some songs even available for full length listening. Online music stores typically show a picture of the album art or of the performer or band for each song. Some online music stores also sell recorded speech files, such as podcasts, and video files of movies.

Francisco Bustamante (born December 29, 1963) is a Filipino professional pool player from Tarlac, Central Luzon and the 2010 World Nine-ball Champion, nicknamed "Django", after the lead character of the 1966 film of the same name, and sometimes also called "Bustie", especially in the United States. Francisco Bustamante has won over 50 International titles.
